A. Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv ./venv
this will create a folder environment called venv that contains all the dependencies.
1. activate virtual env.
source .venv/bin/activate
2. deactivate virtual env.
deactivate

3. Make sure to be in venv environment. Now install django
pip install django
4.

B. Create database
1. Download Postgres
For Mac, go to: https://postgresapp.com/
2. Open Postgres. Make sure the server is running.
2.1. Click on postgres
\password postgres to set up the user postgres
2.2. Create Database
CREATE DATABASE ismp OWNER postgres;
\l to see all database
2.3. Optional
Install pgadmin here: https://www.pgadmin.org/
Follow intruction to see database in website


